# --- hive runtime (repo-local state that must not be committed) ---
# .hive/memory and .hive/skills ARE committed by design (see SPEC.md);
# only ephemeral agent worktrees and runtime state are ignored.
.hive/worktrees/
.hive/*.db
.hive/*.pid

#Coding Agents
.claude/worktrees
.codex/
# hive writes per-worktree MCP wiring at spawn (see writeClaudeAgentConfig)
.mcp.json
# hive symlinks shared skills into each worktree at spawn (see
# src/adapters/skills.ts); not anchored to .hive/worktrees/ because this
# file is evaluated from each worktree's own root, where that path never
# matches.
.agents/
# The Claude-native equivalents of the two rules above: hive writes
# .claude/settings.local.json (writeClaudeAgentConfig) and symlinks skills
# into .claude/skills/ at spawn, so an unignored entry makes every Claude
# worktree look dirty and blocks hive_kill cleanup. Committed skill symlinks
# stay tracked; add new intentional ones with `git add -f`.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/skills/
